03:03.201 --> 03:07.204
<i>[Woman Singing In French]</i>

03:07.238 --> 03:10.173
<i>♪</i>

03:10.208 --> 03:13.276
[Crowd Chatter]

03:16.180 --> 03:18.348
Where is she, you sadistic freak?

03:18.382 --> 03:19.883
Karma.

03:19.917 --> 03:21.318
When I dropped her off at Kane Hill,

03:21.352 --> 03:22.886
that place was halfway normal.

03:22.920 --> 03:25.322
- [Blow Thumps]
- [Grunts]

03:25.356 --> 03:29.192
And now I find that
it's a sugar-fiend shit show.

03:30.595 --> 03:33.430
Someone checked her out.

03:33.464 --> 03:35.499
Who was it?

03:35.533 --> 03:37.367
Kane Hill?

03:37.401 --> 03:40.203
Kane Hill... sounds familiar.

03:42.707 --> 03:45.342
You were the goddamn
hospital administrator.

03:45.376 --> 03:47.344
<i>[Dramatic Musical Sting]</i>

03:47.378 --> 03:48.612
Ooh.

03:48.646 --> 03:50.380
How's that even possible?

03:50.414 --> 03:54.417
Oh, I wear many hats.

03:54.452 --> 03:56.720
I see.

03:56.754 --> 03:58.355
This isn't working.

03:58.389 --> 03:59.523
It's just turning him on.

03:59.557 --> 04:02.459
Oh, the good Cop, my hero.

04:02.493 --> 04:05.395
He knows the truth, Barbie.

04:05.429 --> 04:07.364
And I'm gonna beat it out of him.

04:07.398 --> 04:10.267
Okay, well, why don't you let
me ask him some questions

04:10.301 --> 04:11.735
while he still has some teeth?

04:11.769 --> 04:13.937
Okay.

04:13.971 --> 04:16.206
What does Heart want
with medical facilities

04:16.240 --> 04:18.975
and what does that have to do
with patients like Karma?

04:19.010 --> 04:20.610
Tell me how they're connected.

04:20.644 --> 04:23.446
♪ The neck bone's connected to the ♪

04:23.481 --> 04:25.248
♪ Shoulder bone ♪

04:25.283 --> 04:27.617
♪ The shoulder bone's connected to the ♪

04:27.652 --> 04:29.486
♪ Rib bone ♪

04:29.520 --> 04:31.955
[Softly] ♪ The neck bone's
connected to the ♪

04:31.989 --> 04:34.958
[Intense Dubstep Music Plays]

04:34.992 --> 04:37.427
♪

04:37.461 --> 04:38.562
[Cheering]

04:38.596 --> 04:44.634
♪

04:46.604 --> 04:49.005
You really think he's here, sis?

04:49.040 --> 04:51.441
Take a look.
This place has Slink written...

04:51.475 --> 04:53.009
TOGETHER: All over it.

04:53.044 --> 04:54.778
Why would he come back?

04:54.812 --> 04:56.746
Doesn't look like
he's honoring the dead.

04:56.781 --> 04:58.582
Well, whatever the reason,

04:58.616 --> 05:00.283
thank God he came back to Meadeville.

05:00.318 --> 05:01.785
We never would have found him.

05:01.819 --> 05:04.254
We don't even know what he looks like.

05:04.288 --> 05:06.590
[Crowd Chanting]
Slink! Slink! Slink! Slink!

05:06.624 --> 05:08.425
Well, we're about to find out.

05:08.459 --> 05:12.596
[Chanting Continues]
Slink! Slink! Slink! Slink!

05:12.630 --> 05:14.631
Slink! Slink! Slink! Slink!

05:14.665 --> 05:16.499
Come on, Jackie Boy.

05:16.534 --> 05:18.602
TOGETHER: Let's rock and roll.

05:18.636 --> 05:20.604
Slink! Slink! Slink! Slink!

05:20.638 --> 05:24.007
[Chanting Continues In Background]

05:24.041 --> 05:27.611
[Uneven, Rapid Breathing]

05:29.847 --> 05:32.616
[Metal Doors Clattering]

05:32.650 --> 05:34.484
[Clank]

05:36.554 --> 05:39.022
[Singsong] How's our newest asset?

05:39.056 --> 05:40.724
Stay away from me.

05:40.758 --> 05:42.659
[Doors Rumble Shut]

05:46.697 --> 05:50.033
Come out, Christopher.

05:50.067 --> 05:51.635
<i>[Dainty Ambient Music]</i>

05:51.669 --> 05:53.370
You must be cold in that gown.

05:53.404 --> 05:56.640
I brought new, clean clothes
just for you.

05:56.674 --> 05:58.642
No more tests.

05:58.676 --> 06:00.477
We're done with all that.

06:00.511 --> 06:01.645
No more needles.

06:01.679 --> 06:04.481
No experiments of any kind.

06:04.515 --> 06:09.653
<i>♪</i>

06:09.687 --> 06:11.521
I promise.

06:18.696 --> 06:20.463
That's it.

06:23.868 --> 06:27.704
Your eye is ready.

06:27.738 --> 06:29.706
[Instrument Clinks]

06:35.880 --> 06:39.749
I only want to take off your bandage.

06:39.784 --> 06:41.851
<i>[Dainty Ominous Music]</i>

06:41.886 --> 06:44.854
So, please, try to relax.

06:44.889 --> 06:50.860
<i>♪</i>

06:50.895 --> 06:52.896
Your partner may have abandoned you,

06:52.930 --> 06:55.865
but we at Heart Enterprises
take care of our own.

06:55.900 --> 07:00.136
Your cooperation hasn't gone unnoticed.

07:00.171 --> 07:07.410
<i>♪</i>

07:09.000 --> 07:15.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:16.754 --> 07:19.756
You're good as new.

07:24.795 --> 07:26.663
Here.

07:26.697 --> 07:29.599
See for yourself.

07:29.633 --> 07:31.568
[Sighs]

07:33.771 --> 07:37.407
Say hello to Christopher 2.0.

07:37.441 --> 07:40.410
<i>[Ominous Music]</i>

07:40.444 --> 07:43.613
[Screams]

07:43.647 --> 07:46.583
[Both Screaming]

07:46.617 --> 07:49.486
Tell you what, let me do my job,

07:49.520 --> 07:52.589
and I'll pretend this little
interrogation never happened.

07:52.623 --> 07:54.958
Not until you tell us the truth...

07:54.992 --> 07:56.760
about Karma, about Heart,

07:56.794 --> 07:59.662
about all the messed-up things
you people have ever done.

07:59.697 --> 08:01.931
The world's gone to hell,
Officer Krupke.

08:01.966 --> 08:03.933
We're the norm now. You're the anomaly.

08:03.968 --> 08:04.968
Why don't you just accept it?

08:05.002 --> 08:06.603
Because that's not true.

08:06.637 --> 08:07.771
Not everyone's as bad as you.

08:07.805 --> 08:10.774
Show me one unsullied thing

08:10.808 --> 08:12.942
on this septic tank of a planet.

08:12.977 --> 08:15.612
<i>[Brooding Music]</i>

08:15.646 --> 08:17.514
Ah.

08:17.548 --> 08:18.848
- And I'm not the only one.
- [Chuckles]

08:18.883 --> 08:21.217
Christopher,
wherever you're keeping him,

08:21.252 --> 08:22.852
he's a good Cop too.

08:22.887 --> 08:27.457
Oh, Gracie, piggy here
thinks he's a poster boy.

08:27.491 --> 08:30.727
Well, that Action Man
costume's not fooling me

08:30.761 --> 08:32.962
for one second, Arthur dear.

08:32.996 --> 08:35.732
I think we both know who you really are.

08:35.765 --> 08:37.200
<i>♪</i>

08:37.234 --> 08:38.701
They're getting rowdy out there.

08:38.736 --> 08:39.803
It won't be long before they

08:39.837 --> 08:41.671
come in here and trash the place.

08:41.705 --> 08:43.472
<i>Slink! Slink! Slink! Slink!</i>

08:43.506 --> 08:45.975
Do you hear that, Arthur?
Do you hear that, huh?

08:46.010 --> 08:48.545
That's one big animal horde

08:48.579 --> 08:51.581
that craves carnage.

08:51.615 --> 08:55.485
One giant, rotting circus.

08:55.519 --> 08:56.820
And I'm P.T. Barnum.

08:56.854 --> 08:58.254
Where you going?

08:58.289 --> 09:00.857
To tame the lions.

09:00.891 --> 09:03.993
Slink! Slink! Slink! Slink!

09:04.028 --> 09:07.697
Good evening, Mayhemers!

09:07.731 --> 09:09.666
Let's hear it for your

09:09.700 --> 09:12.936
Master of Ceremonies.

09:12.970 --> 09:14.704
[Crickets Chirping]

09:14.738 --> 09:17.240
[Microphone Feedback Whine]

09:17.274 --> 09:21.010
Uh...

09:21.045 --> 09:22.946
Who's ready for a good time?

09:22.980 --> 09:25.014
- You suck!
- [Scattered Laughter]

09:25.049 --> 09:27.717
- You suck!
- [Crowd Booing]

09:27.751 --> 09:28.718
[Glass Smashing]

09:28.752 --> 09:29.953
Okay... ah.

09:29.987 --> 09:31.588
That hurts.

09:31.622 --> 09:33.690
That hurt... excuse me, that hurts.

09:33.724 --> 09:37.861
Uh, is it getting hot in here,
or is it, uh, just me?

09:37.895 --> 09:41.564
<i>[Light, Whimsical Whistling]</i>

09:41.599 --> 09:42.599
Slink.

09:42.633 --> 09:44.267
I don't know, Diane.

09:44.301 --> 09:45.935
He doesn't look like a mass murderer.

09:45.970 --> 09:48.738
Yeah, well, he's a trickster by trade.

09:48.772 --> 09:50.540
Don't let him fool you.

09:50.574 --> 09:51.541
That's Slink.

09:51.575 --> 09:52.909
- Okay.
- [Crowd Booing]

09:52.943 --> 09:54.878
Uh, tough crowd, tough...

09:54.912 --> 09:56.279
tough crowd.

09:56.313 --> 09:58.648
Okay, jeez... uh... Okay...

09:58.682 --> 10:01.317
Uh... a guy sits down on a bus,

10:01.352 --> 10:03.052
and he's very frustrated...

10:03.087 --> 10:05.788
When is it okay to kill?

10:05.823 --> 10:08.958
[Arthur Continues Talking In Background]

10:11.829 --> 10:13.830
"When it's for love."

10:13.864 --> 10:17.734
<i>[Uplifting Music]</i>

10:17.768 --> 10:18.735
All right.

10:18.769 --> 10:19.936
Let's do it.

10:19.970 --> 10:21.638
- For mother...
- [Together] And father.

10:21.672 --> 10:23.072
Wait.

10:23.107 --> 10:25.642
We'll never get to him
through this crowd.

10:25.676 --> 10:26.910
We're gonna have to

10:26.944 --> 10:30.313
thin the herd.

10:30.347 --> 10:32.682
The plan was to kill Slink,
not a whole party.

10:32.716 --> 10:34.918
Well, they might try and stop us.

10:34.952 --> 10:37.587
So why don't we give them the kiss

10:37.621 --> 10:38.955
and let the virus do its job?

10:38.989 --> 10:41.090
And then we take him out

10:41.125 --> 10:43.793
when there is nobody left...

10:43.827 --> 10:44.928
[Together] To stop us.

10:44.962 --> 10:46.362
Good.

10:46.397 --> 10:47.830
Now, remember,

10:47.865 --> 10:49.766
lay it on thick.

10:49.800 --> 10:51.668
<i>[Schmaltzy Pop Music]</i>

10:51.702 --> 10:53.603
<i>[Ominous Sting]</i>

10:53.637 --> 10:55.638
<i>♪ Forever ♪</i>

10:55.673 --> 10:56.806
<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

10:56.840 --> 10:59.108
<i>♪ Yes, I'll wait forever ♪</i>

10:59.143 --> 11:00.977
Welcome to Meadeville.

11:01.011 --> 11:03.980
<i>[Ominous Whistling]</i>

11:04.014 --> 11:06.983
<i>♪</i>

11:10.460 --> 11:12.493
What the hell'd you do to me?

11:12.528 --> 11:14.228
Think of it as a metaphor

11:14.263 --> 11:16.564
for Heart Enterprises
becoming a part of you.

11:16.598 --> 11:18.366
<i>[Ambient Music]</i>

11:18.400 --> 11:21.202
That isn't how a metaphor works.

11:21.236 --> 11:23.838
In the outside world,
you may have considered yourself

11:23.872 --> 11:26.641
an individual, but here at Heart,

11:26.675 --> 11:28.843
you'll be a small component

11:28.877 --> 11:32.180
of something far greater.

11:32.214 --> 11:34.415
Not interested.

11:34.449 --> 11:36.551
I'm going home.

11:36.585 --> 11:38.853
Okay.

11:38.887 --> 11:40.188
<i>♪</i>

11:40.222 --> 11:42.223
- Really?
- Of course.

11:42.257 --> 11:43.391
You're free to go.

11:43.425 --> 11:46.360
<i>[Soft Dramatic Music]</i>

11:46.395 --> 11:48.863
But not before you settle up.

11:48.897 --> 11:51.866
[Voice Distorting]
That eye cost $20 million.

11:51.900 --> 11:56.237
<i>[Ominous Chords]</i>

11:56.271 --> 12:03.211
<i>♪</i>

12:03.245 --> 12:04.879
[Punk Rock Music Playing]

12:04.913 --> 12:06.614
[Crowd Booing]

12:06.648 --> 12:09.450
Ah... oh, okay.

12:09.484 --> 12:11.586
This looks like somebody had
a little too much sugar today.

12:11.620 --> 12:14.689
<i>[Music, Crowd Muffled]</i>

12:17.259 --> 12:18.359
[Metallic Clank]

12:21.930 --> 12:22.897
[Clinking]

12:22.931 --> 12:23.898
Pour us a glass of wine.

12:23.932 --> 12:25.933
We'll make a night of it.

12:25.968 --> 12:27.301
What are you?

12:27.336 --> 12:28.236
I told you,

12:28.270 --> 12:31.372
I exist for one reason
and one reason alone.

12:31.406 --> 12:33.608
I am the Master of Mayhem,
Captain of Chaos,

12:33.642 --> 12:36.644
God of the Stage.

12:36.678 --> 12:38.946
